cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.SD, cs.MM, cs.CY 

This paper deals with identifying spam campaigns on YouTube, which involves analyzing networks derived from comments posted by users to videos. This falls under the category of social media analysis, which is often associated with the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.SD (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing video content, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves tracking the activity of spam user accounts over time, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
